geschichtsfrkl: a biblatex bibliography style for (German) historians with lots of options

Copyright (C) 2011--2016 Jonathan Zachhuber
E-mail: jonathan.zachhuber@gmail.com

Files:
geschichtsfrkl.ins      Batch file, run through LaTeX
geschichtsfrkl.dtx      Docstrip archive, run through (Xe)LaTeX
geschichtsfrkl.bbx	biblatex bibliography style file, generated by geschichtsfrkl.ins from geschichtsfrkl.dtx
geschichtsfrkl.cbx	biblatex citation style file, generated by geschichtsfrkl.ins from geschichtsfrkl.dtx
geschichtsfrkl.pdf      Package documentation; can also be generated from geschichtsfrkl.dtx
README                  This file

This material is subject to the LaTeX Project Public License. See
http://www.ctan.org/tex-archive/help/Catalogue/licenses.lppl.html for the
details of that license.

Run the Batch file through LaTeX to extract the bbx and cbx files. If desired, uncomment the directory options in the file (and/or change them to your directory of choice) to have the files placed in different directories. Note that these directories have to exist, though.

To create the documentation, run the dtx file through (Xe)LaTeX (the XeLaTeX version uses the Linux Libertine font, though, so make sure you have that installed, otherwise use pdflatex). To generate the index and Change History, use e.g.

makeindex -s gglo.ist -o geschichtsfrkl.gls geschichtsfrkl.glo
makeindex -s gind.ist -o geschichtsfrkl.ind geschichtsfrkl.idx

For more information on the package, see the documentation in geschichtsfrkl.pdf (unfortunately, it is in German, especially the examples should be fairly self-explanatory, though; feel free to contact me for english translations).